<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880812-0064 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Claris Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AAPL </CO><IN> EDP </IN><TEXT>   Claris Corp., the software unit of Apple Computer Inc., unveiled a computer-aided design program for Apple's Macintosh personal computers.    The new software, which will be available in the fourth quarter for a suggested retail price of $799, is part of Apple's continuing efforts to diversify its customer base. The Macintosh has made successful inroads into the office-computer marketplace, and the new CAD program is meant to win away architects, engineers and scientists who have flocked to upstart computer-workstation makers like Sun Microsystems Inc.    Claris is based in Mountain View, Calif. </TEXT></DOC>